  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Operational support for Peacebuilding opportunities during times of COVID-19.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will adopt the POF (Peacebuilding opportunities fund) project to COVID 19 through CAFOD, CRN, SSBS-HD through Bakhita Radio station in Juba with repeat of talk shows done in other Diocesan Radios in South Sudan. The project will focus on peacebuilding, identifying opportunities for peacebuilding, social adjustments in cultural and social practices and COVID-19 health matters. Discussions will also focus on GBV through engagement of community leaders, opinion leaders and general citizens through educative messaging, interviews with peacebuilding, health and gender programming experts. 
There will be interactive discussions on various themes including peace building, GBV and COVID-19 infection risk reduction measures to ensure that accurate information is available to affected populations in an accessible and culturally appropriate manner. There will be sessions for radio talk shows, question and answer sessions with peace building, health and gender experts, vox pops, radio dramas, songs and jingles to pass on information and messages.</narrative>
  </description>
